args.canonical_rel_desc: Indicates that the subject is a constituent, sub-aspect, or component of the object within a broader whole (which may be a concept, practice, belief system, or other structured entity).
args.justification: All three relations describe a clear part-whole or aspect-whole membership: burial practices as part of Egyptian culture, mummification as an aspect of burial practices, and the realm of the gods as a component/destination within afterlife beliefs. These are best normalized under a single canonical predicate expressing conceptual part-whole structure.

Each relation links an aspect, component, or sub-domain to a larger cultural or religious whole, which fits a generic part-whole relation class that can cover conceptual and practice-based hierarchies.

The semantics concern how broader entities (culture, burial practices, afterlife beliefs) are composed from sub-practices, sub-aspects, or sub-realms, which aligns with a compositional/part-whole grouping.
